{"lemma":"شَيْخَيْ","slug":"شَيْخَيْ","root":"ش.#.خ","root_slug":"ش-_-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَيْخ","root":"شيخ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23480","n23482"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old man"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"elderly gentleman, elder"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sheik, chief, chieftain, patriarch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"senator"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sheik; Dr.; professor (title of professors and spiritual leaders)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sir (respectful title of address)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master (someone outstanding or excellent)","examples":[{"text":"شَيْخُ الشَّباب","english":"the greatest of all guys"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃajx/","/ʃeːx/","[ʃe̞ːx]"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23480","headword_ar":"شيّخ","root":"$yx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the preceding paragraph.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$y~xhu","text_ar":"شيّخهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oyiyxN","text_ar":"تَشْيِيخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called him by the appellation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayox","text_ar":"شَيْخ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to pay him honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$y~x Ealayohi","text_ar":"شيّخ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with, a vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault; blamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reproached, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast a bad, an evil, a foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excessively bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul, imputation upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$y~x bihi","text_ar":"شيّخ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$y~xhu","text_ar":"شيّخهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~axotu Alrjl","text_ar":"شَيَّخْتُ الرجل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as on the authority of AZ, in the TA, but this may be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$y~xt biAlr~ajuli","text_ar":"شيّخت بِالرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exposed his vices, faults,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil actions; disgraced him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put him to shame."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23482","headword_ar":"شَيْخٌ","root":"$yx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, L, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxuwnN","text_ar":"شَيْخُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but the latter is a strange word, mentioned by some of the expositors of the Fs, as expressing more than the former word, (MF,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elderly, man; an elder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man whose age gives him a claim to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect; a senior;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one advanced in age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is beyond him who is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaholN","text_ar":"كَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which means him whose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAb","text_ar":"شَبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthfulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prime of manhood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is ended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in whom age has become apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and hoariness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man from the age of fifty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fifty-one, to the end of his life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the age of eighty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) also expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man advanced in age but having strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vigour, to fight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and weak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a decrepit, man, who is of no service:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [in the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the senses above mentioned; and is also especially applied, as an appellation of honour, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a doctor of religion and law; a head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, of a religious confraternity; a chief of a tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a village;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reputed saint:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] fem. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxapN","text_ar":"شَيْخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aged, woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajuwzN","text_ar":"عَجُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) [and applied in the present day particularly to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a learned woman; an instructress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. [of pauc.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oyaAxN","text_ar":"اَشْيَاخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyxapN","text_ar":"شِيخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, ISd, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uyuwxN","text_ar":"شُيُوخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyuwxN","text_ar":"شِيُوخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, with kesr, to agree with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyxaAnN","text_ar":"شِيخَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyaxapN","text_ar":"شِيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayaxapN","text_ar":"شَيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A [there said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabadapN","text_ar":"عَبَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, and so in one of my copies of the S,) or this last is a quasi-pl. n., (Mgh, Msb,) and [so are] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مِشْيَخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيُخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$oyuxapN","text_ar":"مِشْيُخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iyxapN","text_ar":"مَشِيخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and so in one of my copies of the S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuwxaA='u","text_ar":"مَشْيُوخَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the last like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuwHaA='u","text_ar":"مَشْيُوحَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoluwjaA='u","text_ar":"مَعْلُوجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoluwmaA='u","text_ar":"مَسْلُومَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobuwdaA='u","text_ar":"مَعْبُودَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwraA='u","text_ar":"مَعْيُورَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are said to be the only other instances of this form, (TA,) [but to these should be added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHomuwraA='u","text_ar":"مَحْمُورَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makobuwraA='u","text_ar":"مَكْبُورَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"matoyuwsaA='u","text_ar":"مَتْيُوسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and perhaps some other instances,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuxaA='u","text_ar":"مَشْيُخَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and another pl. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAyixu","text_ar":"مَشَايِخُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) or this last is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) and is disallowed by IDrd and Kz (TA) [though very commonly used in the present day, especially as applied to doctors of religion and law]; and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oyaAxN","text_ar":"اَشْيَاخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAyiyxu","text_ar":"اَشَايِيخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAyiybu","text_ar":"اَنَايِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Z, TA:) the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uyayoxN","text_ar":"شُيَيْخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyayoxN","text_ar":"شِيَيْخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uwayoxN","text_ar":"شُوَيْخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not allowable, (S, A,) or is rare. (K.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayoxaAni","text_ar":"الشَّيْخَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two Sheykhs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a title peculiarly applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first two Khaleefehs, Aboo-Bekr and 'Omar."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) though young: and in like manner, a man's wife, whether old or young, is called his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajuwz","text_ar":"عَجُوز"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejz","text_ar":"عجز"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  [And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ancestor."},{"kind":"text","text":"Accord. to a copy of the A that seems to have been used by the author of the TA, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wariva mino","text_ar":"وَرِثَ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iyxapi Alkaram","text_ar":"مَشِيخَةِ الكَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A^a$oyaAxihi","text_ar":"من اَشْيَاخِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is tropical, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A=baAy^ihi","text_ar":"مِنْ ا=بَايِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the right reading is evidently ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn ma$iyxatihi","text_ar":"من مَشِيخَتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkarama","text_ar":"الكَرَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inherited, from his ancestors, generosity."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxu Aln~aAri","text_ar":"شَيْخُ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Iblees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because he was created of fire, or because his ultimate place will be the fire of Hell. (Har p. 130.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayoxu","text_ar":"الشَّيْخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mountain-goat that is advanced in age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fullgrown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milk-skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oyaAxu Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"اَشْيَاخُ النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSuwluhaA","text_ar":"اُصُولُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"five"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"planets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAriYo'","text_ar":"دَرَارِىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also applied by some to the five planets,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$yAx Alnjwm","text_ar":"اشياخ النجوم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in this art.,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonaAxu","text_ar":"اَسْنَاخُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is related by Th, (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snx","text_ar":"سنخ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars that do not make their"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temporary"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode in the Mansions of the Moon, which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nujuwmu AlA^axo*i","text_ar":"نُجُومُ الاَخْذِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISd says, I think that he means, by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njwm","text_ar":"نجوم"},{"kind":"text","text":", the fixed stars: Th says that they are called only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonaAxu Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"اَسْنَاخُ النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSuwl","text_ar":"اُصُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof, around which the [other] stars revolve, and pursue their courses. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sinoxN","text_ar":"سِنْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapu","text_ar":"شَجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uyuwxi","text_ar":"الشُّيُوخِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fruit of which is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jirow","text_ar":"جِرْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xir~iyE","text_ar":"خِرِّيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bastard saffron"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapu AlEuSofuri","text_ar":"شَجَرَةُ العُصْفُرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":");"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it grows in the meadows, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroyaAn","text_ar":"قُرْيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places where water runs to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into, meadows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (AZ, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","MF","Mgh","Msb","L","S","A","Kr","ISd","TA","Z"]}]}}